                <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontalignment='0' fontsize='12'>3. Comparing macro conditions</run>
                <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontalignment='0' fontsize='12'>4. Evaluating risk and diversification prospects </run>
                <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontalignment='0' fontsize='12'>5. Recommending final portfolio weights</run>
                <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                <run bold='true' fontalignment='0' fontsize='12'>Data used:</run>
                <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontalignment='0' fontsize='12'>• Yahoo Finance: ETF price history</run>
                <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontalignment='0' fontsize='12'>• iShares / BlackRock: ETF characteristics, holdings, country and industry exposures</run>
                <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontalignment='0' fontsize='12'>• FRED: macroeconomic indicators</run>
                <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                <run bold='true' fontalignment='0' fontsize='12'>Python</run>
                <run fontalignment='0' fontsize='12'> is used for initial preprocessing and portfolio optimization</run>
                <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                <run bold='true' fontalignment='0' fontsize='12'>Tableau</run>
