    <dashboard name='ETF Allocation Decision Story' type='storyboard'>
      <style />
      <size maxheight='700' maxwidth='1300' minheight='700' minwidth='1300' preset-index='1' sizing-mode='fixed' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='100000' id='2' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
          <zone h='97714' id='1' param='vert' removable='false' type-v2='layout-flow' w='98770' x='615' y='1143'>
            <zone h='4714' id='3' type-v2='title' w='98770' x='615' y='1143' />
            <zone fixed-size='104' h='14857' id='4' is-fixed='true' paired-zone-id='5' removable='false' type-v2='flipboard-nav' w='98770' x='615' y='5857' />
            <zone h='78143' id='5' paired-zone-id='4' removable='false' type-v2='flipboard' w='98770' x='615' y='20714'>
              <flipboard active-id='9' nav-type='caption' show-nav-arrows='true'>
                <story-points>
                  <story-point caption='1. Business Task and Data' captured-sheet='0.1 Intro' id='4' />
                  <story-point caption='2. Screen the investable ETF universe' captured-sheet='Dashboard 1' id='2'>
                    <capturedDeltas>
                      <worksheet name='1.5 ETF Ranking Table'>
                        <selection-collection />
                      </worksheet>
                    </capturedDeltas>
                  </story-point>
                  <story-point caption='3. Understand what the selected ETF actually holds' captured-sheet='Dashboard 2' id='5' />
                  <story-point caption='4. Check macro conditions behind ETF exposure' captured-sheet='Dashboard 3' id='6' />
                  <story-point caption='5. Compare risk, return, drawdowns, and correlations' captured-sheet='Dashboard 4' id='7' />
                  <story-point caption='6. Recommend final optimized ETF allocation' captured-sheet='Dashboard 5' id='8' />
                  <story-point caption='7. Conclusion: from analysis to allocation' captured-sheet='0.2 final' id='9' />
                </story-points>
              </flipboard>
            </zone>
          </zone>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
            <format attr='margin' value='8' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='54000' hidden='true' id='6' story-point-id='2' type-v2='text' w='16692' x='79769' y='29857'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='12'>This dashboard helps reduce the ETF universe to a smaller set of suitable candidates. </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='12'>The decision maker can filter ETFs by development group, style, size, sector and index type. </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='12'>This step supports a controllable decision: which ETFs should be included or excluded before deeper analysis.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='53000' hidden='true' id='7' story-point-id='5' type-v2='text' w='17308' x='79538' y='30143'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='12'>This dashboard analyzes ETF exposure at different levels of detail: country, region, industry cluster, and detailed industry. </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='12'>This is important because an ETF is not just a ticker - it is a basket of countries and sectors. </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='12'>The dashboard helps the decision maker check whether the ETF gives the intended exposure</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='54714' hidden='true' id='8' story-point-id='6' type-v2='text' w='18769' x='78923' y='30429'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='12'>This dashboard adds a macroeconomic explanation layer. </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='12'>For the countries represented in the selected ETF, the decision maker can compare indicators such as inflation, unemployment, interest rates, and exchange rates over time. </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='12'>This uses both geographic and temporal data to understand whether macro conditions support or weaken the ETF allocation case.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='55857' hidden='true' id='9' story-point-id='7' type-v2='text' w='17846' x='79154' y='30286'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='12'>This dashboard evaluates the screened ETFs using risk-return measures, Sharpe ratio, historical drawdowns, and correlations. </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='12'>It helps the decision maker understand not only which ETFs performed well, but also whether they diversify each other. </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='12'>This step is important because a good portfolio should balance expected return and risk.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='76857' hidden='true' id='10' story-point-id='8' type-v2='text' w='18615' x='78538' y='19429'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontsize='12'>This dashboard turns the previous analysis into a final recommendation. </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontsize='12'>It applies </run>
            <run bold='true' fontalignment='0' fontsize='12'>Markowitz portfolio optimization theory</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontsize='12'> to build an efficient frontier of possible ETF portfolios and select the portfolio with the maximum Sharpe ratio. </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontsize='12'>It shows the selected optimized portfolio, ETF weights, expected return, volatility, Sharpe ratio, drawdown, and final country and industry exposure. </run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontsize='12'>The recommendation follows practical constraints such as long-only weights, risk free rate and a maximum ETF weight.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
      </zones>
      <simple-id uuid='{03674D9A-21ED-467B-9395-95AE9F11AF4A}' />
    </dashboard>
  </dashboards>
